# Browser API Polyfill Protocol

## Pipeline Verification

- Before using modern browser APIs (for example `IntersectionObserver`, `structuredClone`, or `ResizeObserver`), inspect the project build/runtime pipeline to determine whether polyfills are automatically provided.
- Check relevant config and tooling (for example Next.js config, Babel/Webpack setup, and browser target settings) before assuming runtime support.

## Required Recommendation Behavior

- If automatic polyfilling is not present, recommend the required polyfill package and include the import/setup snippet before using the API in generated code.
- Do not introduce compatibility-sensitive browser APIs without confirming either:
  - baseline support for the user-defined browser target, or
  - explicit polyfill setup.

## Example

```tsx
// Add only when the project pipeline does not polyfill this API.
import "intersection-observer";

const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
  // ...
});
```
